OL,3,CEx-Post Office manager apologises for
OL,4,Ccelebrating after sub-postmistress
OL,5,Cjailed
OL,7,FHis email read: "Brilliant news. Well
OL,8,Fdone. Please pass on my thanks to the
OL,9,Fteam."
OL,11,FIn his witness statement to the
OL,12,Finquiry, Mr Smith said his comment of
OL,13,F"brilliant news" was due to the fact
OL,14,Fhe believed "Horizon had been proved
OL,15,Fto be robust" following Mrs Misra's
OL,16,Ftrial.
OL,18,FHe said: "It was intended to be a
OL,19,Fcongratulatory email to the team,
OL,20,Fknowing that they had worked hard on
OL,21,Fthe case.
